stylometry: A probability distribution is the likelyhood a certain event may take place given the variables inputted in the model.  The best way for me to describe it would be a baseball teams batting averages.  Each player has a unique batting average, based upon the number of at bats, hits and outs he performed.  Using this data, you can find the standard deviation for the entire team and fairly accuratly determine how well a team will do during a certain period of time.  The model will be more accurate over a longer period of time, like a weeks worth of games, rather than over just one game.
